gomodel:SYNGO_2488  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Results Section: \"ZnT1 concentrates at the postsynaptic density\"\n\n-Literal: \"Particle distribution along the axis perpendicular to the\nsynaptic junction revealed a main peak on the cytoplasmic\nside of the postsynaptic membrane (7.1 ± 0.8 nm from the\nmembrane; n = 339 particles and 132 synapses) (Figure 2F).\"\n\n\"The results indicate that ZnT1 concentrates in the postsynaptic membrane of\nhippocampal synapses,....\"\n\n13/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Fig.1: Seems to be performed in mice: \"BALB/c mice (2 month-old) were anesthesized and perfused ... Hippocampi were collected from postnatal day 1 pups...\"\n\nFig.2+3: Materials and Methods Section: \"Post-embedding immunoelectron microscopy\"\n-Literal:\"For acrylic embedding, brains from two Wistar rats (250-\n300 g) were perfused with 4% formaldehyde...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2488" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

